How can we do that ? 
The way to do that is to develop a conversation with the body . 
We need to learn to speak the body 's language . 
And to switch on processes that we knew how to do when we were a fetus . 
A mammalian fetus , if it loses a limb during the first trimester of pregnancy , will re - grow that limb . 
So our DNA has the capacity to do these kinds of wound - healing mechanisms . 
It 's a natural process , but it is lost as we age . 
In a child , before the age of about six months , if they lose their fingertip in an accident , they 'll re - grow their fingertip . 
